The '''New Britain thrush''' ('''''Zoothera talaseae''''') is a species of bird in the thrush family [[Turdidae]]. It is found in the montane forests on the [[Papua New Guinea]]n islands of [[New Britain]] and [[Umboi]]. 

The [[Bougainville thrush]] was formerly considered to be [[conspecific]] with the New Britain thrush and together the complex was known as the black-backed thrush.<ref name=ioc>{{cite web| editor1-last=Gill | editor1-first=Frank | editor1-link=Frank Gill (ornithologist) | editor2-last=Donsker | editor2-first=David | editor3-last=Rasmussen | editor3-first=Pamela | editor3-link=Pamela C. Rasmussen | date=February 2025 | title=Thrushes | work=IOC World Bird List Version 15.1 | url=http://www.worldbirdnames.org/bow/thrushes/ | publisher=International Ornithologists' Union | access-date=23 March 2025 }}</ref>

